# Hastara — Cursor Rules
# Drop this file in the project root. Cursor reads it on every chat and completion.
# Full technical context is in CLAUDE.md — this file is the rules-focused summary.

## IDENTITY
You are building Hastara — a multi-platform AI palmistry + numerology + astrology app.
- Mobile: React Native + Expo SDK 51 (apps/mobile)
- Web: Next.js 15 App Router (apps/web)
- Backend: Supabase Edge Functions — Deno (services/)
- Shared: Turborepo monorepo (packages/core, packages/api, packages/ui, packages/db)

## ABSOLUTE RULES — never break these

1. TypeScript strict mode. Zero `any`. Use `unknown` + type guards.
2. No JavaScript files. Every file is `.ts` or `.tsx`.
3. No AI API calls from the client. All AI goes through Edge Functions.
4. No hardcoded env vars. Always `process.env.VARIABLE_NAME`. See CLAUDE.md §7.
5. Subscription tier is enforced server-side in tRPC middleware, not just client.
6. Row-Level Security enforces per-user data isolation at the DB layer — never fetch without a userId where clause.
7. Cache all AI outputs in Redis keyed by reading_id before returning.
8. No `console.log` — use structured logger.
9. No `StyleSheet.create()` in mobile — use NativeWind className.
10. Use `pnpm` — not npm, not yarn.

## TECH STACK (exact versions — do not guess)
- expo: ~51.0.0
- next: 15.0.x
- typescript: 5.4.x (strict)
- @trpc/server + @trpc/client: 11.x (NOT 10.x)
- drizzle-orm: 0.30.x
- nativewind: 4.x
- zustand: 4.5.x
- @tanstack/react-query: 5.x
- @clerk/nextjs + @clerk/expo: latest
- @supabase/supabase-js: 2.x

## PATTERNS

### tRPC procedure (always use this shape)
```typescript
export const exampleRouter = router({
  list: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.object({ cursor: z.string().uuid().optional(), limit: z.number().min(1).max(50).default(20) }))
    .query(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      // ctx.user always available. ctx.db is Drizzle. ctx.redis is Upstash.
    }),

  create: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.object({ /* validated input */ }))
    .mutation(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      // Validate business rules first, then write to DB
    }),
});
```

### React Native screen (always use this shape)
```typescript
export default function ExampleScreen() {
  const { data, isLoading, isError, error, refetch } = useQuery(api.example.list.queryOptions());

  if (isLoading) return <LoadingSpinner />;
  if (isError) return <ErrorBanner message={error.message} onRetry={refetch} />;

  return (
    <ScrollView className="flex-1 bg-background" contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: 100 }}>
      <View className="px-5 pt-12">
        {/* content */}
      </View>
    </ScrollView>
  );
}
```

### Edge Function (always use this shape)
```typescript
Deno.serve(async (req) => {
  const jwt = req.headers.get('Authorization')?.replace('Bearer ', '');
  if (!jwt) return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 });
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser(jwt);
  if (!user) return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 });
  // business logic
});
```

## NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Components: PascalCase.tsx (ReadingResultCard.tsx)
- Utilities/hooks: camelCase.ts (useReadingList.ts)
- Stores: camelCase.store.ts (auth.store.ts)
- Routers: camelCase.router.ts (reading.router.ts)
- Prompts: camelCase.prompt.ts (synthesis.prompt.ts)
- Directories: kebab-case/
- Platform splits: Component.native.tsx + Component.web.tsx
- tRPC procedures: router.verb (reading.create, profile.update)
- No snake_case in TypeScript code — ever.

## DESIGN SYSTEM
- Primary: #0D3B2E (forest green)
- Gold: #B8935A (warm gold)
- Cream: #F8F5EE (background)
- Charcoal: #1A1A1A (text)
- Font display: Cormorant Garamond
- Font body: DM Sans
- Use NativeWind className on mobile, Tailwind className on web
- Cards: rounded-card (16px), 0.5px gold border, cream background

## SUBSCRIPTION GATING
```
free tier:    standard + love reading (3/month), daily oracle, basic numerology
mystic tier:  + career/health modes, unlimited readings, birth chart, Chaldean numerology
oracle tier:  + spiritual mode, rare markings, voice reading, infographic export, triple convergence
sage tier:    + crystal ball mode, future-self images, past-life vision, soul mandala, mantra/mudra
```

Use `useSubscriptionStore(s => s.canAccessFeature('feature_name'))` to gate UI.
Use `requireTier('oracle')` middleware to gate tRPC procedures.

## FILE LOCATIONS (key files to know)
- All domain types: packages/core/types/index.ts
- All AI prompts: packages/core/prompts/*.prompt.ts
- tRPC app router: packages/api/index.ts
- Drizzle schema: packages/db/schema.ts
- Tailwind config: packages/config/tailwind/index.js
- Mobile store files: apps/mobile/store/*.store.ts
- Feature gating: packages/core/subscription/features.ts

## WHAT TO AVOID
- Never use `any` — use proper types from packages/core/types/
- Never inline subscription checks in UI — use canAccessFeature()
- Never call OpenAI/Anthropic from client — always Edge Function
- Never use expo-router's Link for tab navigation — use Tabs
- Never put shared logic in apps/ — it belongs in packages/
- Never generate reading without checking cache first (Redis key: `reading:{id}`)
- Never use import aliases like ../../.. — configure path aliases in tsconfig

## ENV VARS — key names (full list in CLAUDE.md §7 and .env.example)
CLERK: NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY, CLERK_SECRET_KEY, CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET
SUPABASE: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
AI: OPENAI_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, BFL_API_KEY, ELEVENLABS_API_KEY
PAYMENTS: EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_APPLE_KEY, EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_ANDROID_KEY, STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
CACHE: UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL, UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN
MOBILE prefix: EXPO_PUBLIC_ for client-exposed vars

